examples.detail:
bridge edge-case (#533) — for header-only single-line files
the bridge emits 1 spurious Block even with sendHeaderMode=0;
native correctly emits 0. Spec asserts native behavior.

bridge default config strips printf placeholders (`%d`)
from the source text via Okapi's default code-finder rules,
yielding " files" instead of "%d files". Native treats the
msgid as literal text under the standard PO config (matching
the inlines_passthrough feature). Both legitimate;
spec asserts native behavior.

Escape decoding divergence — same as escaped_quotes. The
bridge extracts both Blocks but leaves `\\n` / `\\t` literal;
native decodes \\n → LF and \\t → TAB inside captured text.

bridge LF-collapse divergence (#536) — bridge consumes the LF
on the spliced line, emitting "Continued line" for block 1;
native preserves it. Spec asserts native semantics.
